===Etymology===
The first part of the verb, ''driz-'' comes probably from Middle English ''drēse'', Old English ''[[drēosan]]''
===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|drizzl|e|}}

# To [[rain]] lightly

====Translations====
*Czech; [[mrholit]]
*French; [[bruiner]]
*Hungarian: [[(eső) csepereg]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# Light rain
# {{Physics}} ([[Weather]]). Very small, [[numerous]], and [[uniform]]ly dispersed [[water]] [[drops]], [[mist]], or [[sprinkle]]. Unlike [[fog]] [[droplets]], drizzle falls to the ground. It is sometimes accompanied by low [[visibility]] and fog. 

